name: Route 66

reviews.review_text:
We stopped at Route 66 for a very late lunch after looking up the restaurant on Google. Since it was an odd hour it was sparse with just one other group. I was quite impressed by the striking interiors and artwork to reflect the pan-American cuisine. The space is open and inviting with the dining furniture comprising solid tables and chairs as well as diner style booths.
The staff was courteous and accommodating. We had dietary restrictions and the chef was able to conform to our requests. The food quality and taste was not compromised. Our custom order thin crust vegan pizza was a winner!
The cocktails are amazing.
A special shout out to Chetana for ensuring our experience was enjoyable!

Theme and ambience were good but the seats seamed like they weren't cleaned in a long time and had dust all over it.
They have very limited options for chicken lovers but they do give an option of replacing the patty with a chicken one, so that's good. We ordered the Route 66 burger and Veg primavera pizza - both of which were amazing. Price was on the higher side though.
The cocktails were poorly made with bad taste. Not worth the price at all.
Won't recommend this place for drinks but only for the food.

Went to Route 66 after a spade of years. They used to be known for their hamburgers and steaks. The decor is bit confusing between a pop-rock and Texan style and bit dated looking. However the 90s music was really nice. The hamburgers luckily were still the old style way and they had not lost their touch here. Served typically with a knife to cut the hamburger. Had the chicken roxette, pork fat boy and beef route 66 special served with old style coke bottles.

description:
**Introduction & Overview**  
Nestled in the heart of Panaji, Route 66 stands out with an impressive rating of 4.3, complemented by a robust 1,900 reviews from enthusiastic patrons. This lively café is celebrated for its inviting ambience, delectable cheesecakes, and crowd-favorite nachos, making it a go-to spot for both casual outings and special treats. The restaurant artfully blends a vibrant décor inspired by Pan-American culture, with the eclectic menu offering a delightful array of options for all palates.

**Ambiance & Design**  
Upon entering Route 66, guests are greeted by a visually striking interior adorned with artwork that celebrates the spirit of pop-rock and Texan flair. Although some noted that the décor might feel a bit dated and somewhat confusing, it manages to create a welcoming and fun atmosphere perfect for dining. The space is thoughtfully laid out with solid tables, comfortable chairs, and retro-style diner booths. One customer mentioned enjoying the 90s music that fills the air, adding a nostalgic touch to the dining experience. However, some guests pointed out that cleanliness could use improvement, particularly with seating that seemed neglected.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  
Route 66 is particularly renowned for its signature burgers and pizzas. Reviews highlight favorites like the Route 66 burger, a standout for both its flavors and nostalgic presentation with an old-style Coke bottle on the side. Another guest praised the thin crust vegan pizza, crafted to perfection even when accommodating dietary restrictions. The menu features a limited range for chicken lovers but offers flexibility with substitutes for many dishes. While the presentation of the food is appealing, some diners felt the prices were on the higher side. On the sweet side, the cheesecake has become a staple, drawing dedicated fans to this cafe.

**Customer Experience & Service**  
Customer interactions at Route 66 have largely been positive, with many reviews praising the courteous and accommodating staff. Chetana, in particular, was recognized for her attentive service, ensuring that dietary needs were respected without compromising on taste. However, the feedback on cocktails varied significantly, with some customers expressing disappointment in the quality and preparation, leading to a split sentiment regarding the drink menu.

**Popularity & Reviews**  
With an impressive number of reviews and a strong overall rating, Route 66 attracts a diverse crowd, often buzzing with energy. While the restaurant has cultivated a solid social media presence, it continues to rely on repeat customers who love the atmosphere and food. Overall, while some patrons were wary of the drink offerings and cleanliness, the overwhelming sentiment remains positive, especially when it comes to the hearty meals served.

**Utilizing Visual Content**  
The allure of Route 66 is well-captured in customer-provided photos, showcasing the vibrant interior and beautifully presented dishes. The photographs reveal a cozy yet lively setting, emphasizing both the artistic décor and the mouth-watering food. Images of the delectable pizzas and iconic hamburgers align with the enthusiastic descriptions from the reviews, painting a vivid picture of the Route 66 dining experience.

In conclusion, Route 66 remains a beloved dining destination in Panaji, mixing nostalgia with flavorful dishes in a vibrant setting. Whether it's the comforting cheesecakes, hearty burgers, or inviting ambiance, this cafe continually draws lovers of good food and lively experiences, making every visit worthwhile.
